magicbook.gtlitecore.api.utils.reflect

类 StackWalker

  • java.lang.Object
    • magicbook.gtlitecore.api.utils.reflect.StackWalker

  • @ThreadSafe
public final class StackWalker
extends java.lang.Object
    A stack walker, i.e. a fast method to traversing or calling the stack.

    The walk(java.util.function.Function<? super java.util.stream.Stream<magicbook.gtlitecore.api.utils.reflect.StackFrame>, ? extends T>) method opens a sequential stream of StackFrames for the current thread and then applies the given function to walk the StackFrame stream. The stream reports stack frame elements in order, from the top most frame that represents the execution point at which the stack was generated to the bottom most frame. The StackFrame stream is closed when the walk method returns. Throws IllegalArgumentException if an attempt is made to reuse the closed stream.

    The stack walking options of a StackWalker determines the information of StackFrame objects to be returned. By default, stack frames of the reflection API and implementation classes are hidden and StackFrames have the class name and method name available but not the class reference.

    The StackWalker is thread-safe. Multiple threads can share a single StackWalker object to traverse its own stack. A permission check is performed when a StackWalker is created, according to the options it requests. No further permission check is done at stack walking time.

    This is a port version of Java 9 Feature "StackWalker".

    作者:
    Magic_Sweepy

    • 方法详细资料

      • getInstance

        public static StackWalker getInstance(java.util.Set<StackWalker.Option> options)
        Returns a StackWalker instance with the given options specifying the StackFrame information it can access.

        If the given options is empty, this StackWalker is configured to skip all hidden frames and no class reference is retained.

        If a security manager is present and the given options contains RETAIN_CLASS_REFERENCE, it calls its checkPermission method for RuntimePermission("getStackWalkerWithClassReference").

        参数:
        options - Stack walking option in StackWalker.Option.
        返回:
        A StackWalker configured with the given options.
        抛出:
        java.lang.SecurityException - If a security manager exists and its checkPermission method denies access.

      • walk

        public <T> T walk(java.util.function.Function<? super java.util.stream.Stream<StackFrame>,? extends T> walker)
        Applies the given function to the stream of StackFrames for the current thread, traversing from the top frame of the stack, which is the method calling this walk method.

        The StackFrame stream will be closed when this method returns.

        类型参数:
        T - The type of the result of applying the function to the stream of StackFrame.
        参数:
        walker - A function that takes a stream of stack frames and returns a result.
        返回:
        The result of applying the function to the stream of StackFrame.
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - When a closed Stream<StackFrame> object is reused.
